# MySystem — personal Claude Code config
#
# Strategy: ignore everything, whitelist tracked items explicitly.
# External skills (gstack and anything it installs) are NOT whitelisted,
# so they are ignored by default — no maintenance when gstack evolves.
# When adding a user-owned skill, add two lines here (see "User-owned
# skills" section below).

*

# Root files — tracked
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!CLAUDE.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!CONTEXT.md
!README.md
!SETUP.md
!RTK.md
!VERSION
!settings.json
!setup.sh
!install.sh

# Structural directories (whitelisted to let git descend into them)
!skills/
!hooks/
!hooks/**
hooks/__pycache__/
hooks/**/__pycache__/
hooks/**/*.pyc
!templates/
!templates/**
!references/
!references/INDEX.md
!docs/
!docs/**
!.out-of-scope/
!.out-of-scope/**

# User-owned skills — tracked. Add a new entry here when you create one.
# Format: two lines per skill (directory + recursive contents).
# Philosophy: prefer adopting external skills via setup.sh (sparse cherry-pick
# or full external repo) over writing custom ones. Only add here when no
# public alternative exists.
!skills/verify-test/
!skills/verify-test/**
# deep-research — vendored from ECC (was a sparse cherry-pick), now owned + customized. ADR-0011.
!skills/deep-research/
!skills/deep-research/**

# Rules — tracked native `.claude/rules/*.md` path-scoped + always-loaded
# rule files (v0.41.0+, ADR-0009).
!rules/
!rules/**

# Scripts — tracked rollback/ops helpers (v0.38.0+).
!scripts/
!scripts/**

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
.vscode/
